The issue arises because the API is not properly checking for existing reservations before attempting to create a new one. The current implementation overwrites the reservation record with a new one if it already exists, leading to a KeyError when trying to access the old reservation ID. By generating a new unique reservation ID each time and storing it in self._records using the reservation_id as the key, we ensure that each reservation is distinct and can be properly tracked.
